33:35.949 --> 33:37.116
Crazy.

33:38.718 --> 33:40.185
It's over now, baby.

33:40.253 --> 33:42.721
What are y'all
doing over here?

33:42.789 --> 33:44.323
<i># Hey... Go!</i>

33:44.391 --> 33:46.191
<i># Hey... Go!</i>

33:46.259 --> 33:48.060
<i># Hey... Go!</i>

33:48.128 --> 33:49.695
<i># Hey... Go! #</i>

33:51.164 --> 33:52.398
(HISSING)

33:54.734 --> 33:55.701
Hey.

33:55.869 --> 33:56.802
Tommy?

33:58.638 --> 34:00.172
You all right?

34:02.475 --> 34:04.543
I shouldn't have
shot that shit up.

34:07.614 --> 34:09.614
Sarge Shriver.
Sarge King.

34:10.583 --> 34:11.784
(BOTH GRUNTING)

34:16.589 --> 34:17.989
(CHUCKLING)

34:19.359 --> 34:21.293
(EXPLOSION)

34:21.360 --> 34:23.529
Man, I'm gonna
miss blowing shit up.

34:27.333 --> 34:28.634
Next.

34:30.469 --> 34:32.103
Gas mask.
Check.

34:34.674 --> 34:36.007
Poncho liner.
Check.

34:36.076 --> 34:37.509
Sergeant King.

34:37.577 --> 34:40.045
Waterproof bag.
Check.

34:40.112 --> 34:42.880
Did you cover
for me in formation?

34:42.949 --> 34:43.882
Come here.

34:46.920 --> 34:49.154
Look.
Me and Steve
are getting out.

34:49.222 --> 34:52.524
It's up to you and Eyeball
to lead the recruits.

34:52.592 --> 34:54.893
All right.
This new squad leader,
he's a Baptist.

34:54.960 --> 34:57.062
I'm a Baptist.

34:57.130 --> 34:59.832
All right.
He's a real Baptist.

34:59.899 --> 35:02.801
Listen, man,
you got to get
a fucking grip.

35:02.869 --> 35:05.104
You smell like
a fucking brewery.
Come on.

35:05.171 --> 35:08.107
That's 'cause
we were drinking
last night.

35:08.174 --> 35:10.376
Tommy.
Wait! Come on.

35:43.910 --> 35:45.811
WOMAN: Okay.
You're all good to go.

35:52.085 --> 35:55.821
Says here you have
orders to report to
the First Brigade.

35:55.889 --> 35:58.390
Not me.
I'm getting
out today.

35:58.458 --> 36:01.260
Brandon
Leonard King?
Yes.

36:01.327 --> 36:04.029
Out to
the First Brigade
on the 22nd.

36:05.565 --> 36:07.199
This is a mistake.

36:09.035 --> 36:11.036
It's all there.

36:11.104 --> 36:14.640
You leave on the 22nd,
shipping back to Iraq.

36:14.708 --> 36:17.776
Sub-section
12305, Title 10.

36:17.844 --> 36:20.879
By the authority
of the President.

36:20.947 --> 36:22.748
You've been stop-lossed.

36:38.098 --> 36:39.565
Lieutenant Colonel?

36:39.699 --> 36:41.467
Sergeant King.

36:41.534 --> 36:43.769
I teed you up
for a recruitment
pitch in Brazos,

36:43.837 --> 36:45.904
and you gave me
an onion patch.

36:47.540 --> 36:48.640
It's what came
to mind, sir.

36:48.708 --> 36:50.409
What's your problem,
Sergeant?

36:50.477 --> 36:52.311
I'm supposed to
be getting out today.

36:52.379 --> 36:54.179
Now they're shipping
me back to Iraq.

36:54.247 --> 36:56.648
You understand
why it's important
we win over there?

36:56.716 --> 36:58.183
Why we need
good soldiers
like you?

36:58.251 --> 36:59.685
Yes, sir.

36:59.753 --> 37:02.755
You have extenuating
circumstances?
You gay or pregnant?

37:05.558 --> 37:08.327
Sir, you know me.
I'm a squared-away
soldier.

37:08.395 --> 37:10.796
Because I have
an extenuating
circumstance, Sergeant.

37:10.864 --> 37:12.765
It's called a war.
It's in Iraq.

37:12.832 --> 37:15.567
I know, sir.
I volunteered
to fight in it.

37:15.635 --> 37:19.405
I ran over 150 combat
missions for you,
no complaint.

37:19.472 --> 37:23.242
Contract says
stop-loss is only
in a time of war.

37:23.309 --> 37:25.044
This President said
the war's over,
so legally...

37:25.111 --> 37:26.512
You a lawyer, son?

37:26.579 --> 37:27.646
No, sir.

37:27.714 --> 37:29.214
But after doing
right by this Army,

37:29.282 --> 37:32.184
I'm getting burned
by some fine print
in a contract.

37:32.252 --> 37:34.386
Now the President
himself said...
The President is also

37:34.454 --> 37:36.155
the Commander-in-Chief.

37:36.222 --> 37:39.124
I think he trumps
you either way.

37:39.192 --> 37:42.094
With all due respect, sir,
fuck the President!

37:45.031 --> 37:46.365
Fuck the President?

37:46.433 --> 37:49.168
Yes, sir.
He's not over there
fighting this war.

37:49.235 --> 37:52.471
He's not there
seeing his buddies
burned alive in Humvees.

37:52.539 --> 37:54.239
I lost three
men last month,

37:54.307 --> 37:56.675
and I almost got
the rest of us killed.

37:56.743 --> 37:59.311
Those were my men, too,
and I lost more than that.

37:59.379 --> 38:02.948
You're an excellent leader,
and you are going back.

38:03.016 --> 38:04.149
For 11 more years?

38:04.217 --> 38:06.251
It won't come to that.
How do you know?

38:06.319 --> 38:09.021
I think the President
trumps you in
this matter.

38:09.089 --> 38:11.657
This, sir,
is bullshit,
and you know it!

38:15.061 --> 38:19.965
Lieutenant, you just heard
Sergeant King disobey
a direct order.

38:20.033 --> 38:22.835
Yes, sir.
I also perceive him
to be a flight risk.

38:22.902 --> 38:26.105
Escort him to
the stockade so he
can readjust his attitude.

38:26.172 --> 38:27.439
You're making
a big mistake.

38:27.507 --> 38:28.974
I'm doing you
a big favor.

38:29.042 --> 38:30.743
End of discussion.

38:30.810 --> 38:34.380
Make sure he ships
to the First Brigade when
it goes out on the 22nd.

38:34.447 --> 38:35.814
Roger, sir.

39:04.711 --> 39:07.713
Come on, hotshot.
Don't you
fucking touch me!

39:09.416 --> 39:10.416
(SOLDIER GROANS)

39:32.038 --> 39:35.374
Steve, I fucked up real bad.
<i>Hey, man. What?</i>
<i>What'd you do?</i>

39:35.442 --> 39:37.609
I put down a couple guys
and now I'm AWOL.

39:37.677 --> 39:39.144
<i>(STEVE LAUGHS)</i>

39:39.212 --> 39:42.047
<i>What the fuck...</i>
<i>I got stop-lossed</i>
<i>back to Iraq.</i>

39:42.115 --> 39:43.582
<i>Shit!</i>

39:43.650 --> 39:45.417
<i>Oh, okay.</i>
<i>Look, take it to Boot.</i>

39:45.485 --> 39:46.819
<i>You're gold</i>
<i>with him,</i>
<i>he'll fix it.</i>

39:46.886 --> 39:48.687
Yeah, Boot was
trying to send me
to the stockade.

39:48.755 --> 39:51.290
I shook loose
and I took off in
your Jeep, man.

39:51.358 --> 39:54.893
<i>You definitely have</i>
<i>fucked up now.</i>
<i>I know.</i>

39:54.961 --> 39:58.564
I know,
I just got triggered.
I lost my shit.

39:58.631 --> 40:01.467
<i>All right. Wait, look.</i>
<i>All right, get a grip,</i>
<i>calm down.</i>

40:01.534 --> 40:04.737
<i>I'll try to figure out</i>
<i>what's going on here,</i>
<i>and cover your six.</i>

40:04.804 --> 40:06.638
Thanks, man.
I knew you would.

40:06.706 --> 40:08.407
I'll hit you later.

40:56.022 --> 40:57.322
ROY: Come on in, Sheriff.

40:57.390 --> 41:00.192
SHERIFF: Ida,
listen to this.

41:02.295 --> 41:05.597
These MPs came
to me and said
Brandon's gone AWOL.

41:05.665 --> 41:10.002
How in the hell
can he be AWOL if
he's getting out today?

41:10.070 --> 41:11.870
Boot's hopping mad.

41:11.938 --> 41:15.874
He called me personally
to put out a statewide APB.

41:15.942 --> 41:19.478
Get Brandon to turn
himself in and get
this thing sorted out.

41:28.455 --> 41:29.788
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

41:34.527 --> 41:37.663
I don't understand.
They stop-lossed you?

41:37.731 --> 41:38.831
How can they do this?

41:38.898 --> 41:40.632
They're doing whatever
they wanna do.

41:40.700 --> 41:42.301
With a shortage
of guys and no draft,

41:42.369 --> 41:44.770
they're shipping back soldiers
who's supposed to be
getting out.

41:44.838 --> 41:47.339
It's a backdoor
draft, is what it is.

41:47.407 --> 41:48.907
What about Steve?

41:48.975 --> 41:50.542
Mich, I don't know.
Some of us are getting it,
some ain't.

41:50.610 --> 41:52.344
This cannot
be happening.

41:52.412 --> 41:54.246
No! You almost
died over there.

41:54.314 --> 41:55.748
What do you
want to do?

41:55.815 --> 41:56.982
You want me to
take you to Mexico
till this blows over?

41:57.050 --> 41:58.283
No, no, no.
Out of the question, Mom.

41:58.351 --> 42:00.119
I ain't dragging
my tail across
to Mexico.

42:00.186 --> 42:01.987
I'm getting my keys.

42:03.523 --> 42:05.157
Brandon.

42:05.225 --> 42:07.092
Listen to me.
If you're spooked,
it's okay.

42:07.160 --> 42:08.260
There's no
shame in that.

42:08.328 --> 42:11.330
I ain't scared.
I'm pissed off!

42:11.398 --> 42:13.065
This family is done
fighting this war.

42:13.133 --> 42:15.434
He ain't scared, Roy.
He's just being sensible.

42:15.502 --> 42:19.338
I just don't want him
to get in any deeper,
is all.

42:19.406 --> 42:20.739
Maybe ruin
his whole life.

42:20.807 --> 42:22.274
I ain't gonna
let it go that far.

42:22.342 --> 42:24.543
Ruin his life?
How about getting
himself killed?

42:24.611 --> 42:26.345
God damn it, Ida.
Hold on! Hold on!

42:26.413 --> 42:29.148
The Senator said
to my face if I ever
needed anything, he'd help.

42:29.215 --> 42:31.250
That is
a big-ass mistake.

42:31.317 --> 42:33.285
You go out of
the chain of command,
over Boot's head,

42:33.353 --> 42:35.354
you're doubling your trouble.
He's gonna make
an example of you.

42:35.422 --> 42:36.755
I ain't worried
about Boot

42:36.823 --> 42:38.724
once I explain
the whole thing
to the Senator.

42:38.792 --> 42:42.227
I just need to run
up to D.C. right now
and get this sorted out.

42:42.295 --> 42:44.430
Okay. I'll take you.

42:44.497 --> 42:46.665
You can't.
They're gonna be
watching y'all.

42:46.733 --> 42:49.501
They won't be
watching me.
I'll take you.

42:49.569 --> 42:53.005
Michelle, Steve would
have my ass if I let you
get mixed up in all this.

42:53.073 --> 42:55.240
He could be next.

42:55.308 --> 42:57.242
Let's go.
This is wrong,
Brandon.

43:11.624 --> 43:14.226
MICHELLE:
Steve don't talk much
about being over there.

43:17.097 --> 43:18.130
Sand.

43:18.932 --> 43:20.666
Fleas.

43:20.734 --> 43:21.633
Flies.

43:23.436 --> 43:24.837
Heat.

43:24.904 --> 43:26.071
Boredom.

43:27.173 --> 43:29.575
Or you can
get shot at.

43:29.642 --> 43:31.076
Or blown up.

43:32.212 --> 43:34.079
That's pretty much it.

43:37.017 --> 43:38.817
Sheep on the highway.

43:40.453 --> 43:41.220
Where?

43:43.056 --> 43:44.223
In Iraq.

43:45.225 --> 43:46.792
(CHUCKLES)

43:46.860 --> 43:49.028
Big-ass
flocks of them.

43:49.195 --> 43:50.062
Yeah?

43:58.371 --> 44:01.173
Jeanie, it's me.

44:01.241 --> 44:04.243
I need you
to cover my shift
at work tomorrow.

44:04.310 --> 44:05.811
Sorry I woke you up.

44:05.879 --> 44:07.680
<i>No, I was up.</i>
<i>I was up.</i>

44:07.747 --> 44:10.182
<i>And covering your</i>
<i>shift's no problem,</i>

44:10.250 --> 44:12.251
<i>since neither one of us</i>
<i>has a fucking job.</i>

44:12.318 --> 44:14.553
What?
<i>Tommy drove his</i>
<i>car into our work,</i>

44:14.621 --> 44:17.222
<i>drunk as fuck.</i>
<i>He got two DUIs</i>
<i>in the last two days.</i>

44:17.290 --> 44:18.891
What the hell's happening
to these guys?

44:42.682 --> 44:43.782
<i>(PEOPLE SCREAMING)</i>

44:58.765 --> 45:00.733
Are you all right
out here?

45:08.775 --> 45:11.610
I thought I saw somebody
down by the drain.

45:13.179 --> 45:14.046
You okay?

45:16.316 --> 45:17.549
Yeah, sure.

45:20.887 --> 45:22.821
You should try
and get some sleep.

45:28.395 --> 45:30.062
I'll be all right, Mich.

45:37.837 --> 45:39.271
<i>(MACHINE GUNFIRE)</i>

45:46.413 --> 45:47.946
I know what I'm doing.

46:03.463 --> 46:06.265
Listen, Mich, you need
to be getting home.

46:07.567 --> 46:09.234
You need some
dry clothes.

46:14.007 --> 46:16.141
<i>(CHATTERING ON POLICE RADIO)</i>

46:29.923 --> 46:31.523
(OFFICER KNOCKING ON DOOR)

46:31.591 --> 46:33.225
OFFICER: Michelle Overton!

46:35.662 --> 46:37.262
You taught me
everything I know.

46:37.330 --> 46:39.698
You made me
everything I am.

46:39.766 --> 46:43.202
Can't be anything else, sir.
I'm no good as anything else.

46:43.269 --> 46:46.271
DEVER: Then stop
your drinking!
I will, sir.

46:46.339 --> 46:48.640
(DIALING PHONE)
All I wanna be
is a soldier.

46:48.708 --> 46:51.243
I just want to
go back to Iraq.
I'm gonna be better.

46:52.345 --> 46:53.512
Hey, baby.

46:53.580 --> 46:56.181
If I ever...
Put Brandon
on the phone.

46:56.249 --> 46:58.684
<i>Put him</i>
<i>on the phone!</i>
<i>All right.</i>

47:02.355 --> 47:04.857
Hey, man.
<i>Where the hell are you,</i>
<i>man?</i>

47:04.924 --> 47:07.526
I have a situation
you need to step
into right now.

47:07.594 --> 47:09.895
I've been trying to
reach you all night.
Where you been?

47:09.963 --> 47:11.463
I've been at
the fucking jailhouse
all night,

47:11.531 --> 47:13.632
trying to bail Tommy out
of a DUI shitstorm.

47:13.700 --> 47:14.767
God damn it!

47:14.834 --> 47:17.136
Boot is about
to kick Tommy out.

47:17.203 --> 47:20.439
Squad leader is
supposed to be here,
and that's you.

47:20.507 --> 47:22.508
Steve, I can't.

47:22.575 --> 47:24.710
I'm on my way to D.C.
to see the Senator.

47:24.778 --> 47:25.978
<i>You're what?</i>

47:26.046 --> 47:27.312
<i>You're fucking AWOL,</i>

47:27.380 --> 47:29.381
and you're taking Michelle
to fucking D.C.?

47:29.449 --> 47:32.017
I'm gonna cut
her loose at
the state line.

47:32.085 --> 47:33.752
DEVER: You haven't
proved it to me yet!

47:33.820 --> 47:37.356
I need you to handle
this until I get back.
Just a couple of days.

47:37.424 --> 47:39.491
This better be
the last time...
It can't wait that long.

47:39.559 --> 47:41.460
...you drive drunk!
And you, my friend,

47:41.528 --> 47:43.762
<i>you are in deep</i>
<i>fucking shit with Boot.</i>

47:45.331 --> 47:46.432
TOMMY: I'm gonna
make this up.

47:49.636 --> 47:51.236
It's all I got.

47:51.304 --> 47:54.573
This is everything to me.
Army's my family.

47:54.641 --> 47:58.210
I know I'm a little sideways,
but give me one more chance,
please.

48:21.001 --> 48:22.468
What's up?

48:22.535 --> 48:24.703
Gonna head north
on the 55 into
Memphis.

48:24.771 --> 48:26.005
Long way around.

48:26.072 --> 48:28.474
There's something
I got to do.
I'll drive.

49:00.006 --> 49:03.509
In the name of the Father,
the Son and
the Holy Spirit.

49:05.812 --> 49:07.079
MAN 1: Congratulations, man.

49:07.147 --> 49:08.714
MAN 2: It'll take a lot
more than water
till I'm saved.

49:08.782 --> 49:11.183
Thanks, man.
MAN 3: Attaboy, Preacher.
You saved him.

49:13.286 --> 49:15.220
I think you need
some more blessing, bro.

49:15.288 --> 49:16.755
(ALL LAUGHING)

49:28.702 --> 49:32.171
Preacher and the chaplain
baptized a lot of guys
over there.

49:32.238 --> 49:34.239
Come on, sit down.

49:34.307 --> 49:36.909
Just wanted to pay
my respects, sir.

49:36.976 --> 49:39.078
Very grateful
that you came.

49:39.145 --> 49:41.313
You said you
had a bad feeling
about Paul's last tour?

49:41.481 --> 49:42.715
Mmm-hmm.

49:42.782 --> 49:44.483
Why'd he go back
so many times?

49:44.551 --> 49:45.984
He was stop-lossed.

49:47.854 --> 49:49.388
Couldn't find
a way out?

49:49.456 --> 49:52.658
There were people right here
in Memphis on the lay low.

49:52.726 --> 49:55.461
Stop-lossed soldiers
filing a lawsuit.

49:55.528 --> 49:57.830
But he wouldn't listen.

49:57.897 --> 49:59.264
Excuse me.

50:05.939 --> 50:09.308
And how would someone
find these guys with
the lawsuit?

50:11.311 --> 50:13.345
Depends on who
wants to know.

50:16.649 --> 50:18.851
I'd like to know.

50:18.918 --> 50:22.187
It started out just
like any other day.

50:22.255 --> 50:26.925
We were manning a checkpoint,
but we came under attack.

50:26.993 --> 50:31.263
And standard operating
procedure is to pursue
the attackers, and...

50:31.331 --> 50:32.798
Go on,
we want to know.

50:34.334 --> 50:37.369
We followed them
into an alley.

50:37.437 --> 50:39.204
I led my men
into an alley.

50:42.008 --> 50:44.443
Preacher, Paul,
was covering our flank.

50:44.511 --> 50:46.645
We got hit
from both rooftops.

50:48.448 --> 50:51.884
RPGs, small arms,
bullets, explosions...

50:54.788 --> 50:57.589
It was an ambush.

50:57.657 --> 51:01.026
Leading your men into
an ambush is standard
operating procedure?

51:01.094 --> 51:02.594
PASTOR COLSON:
That's enough, Michael.

51:08.702 --> 51:10.936
I remember...

51:11.004 --> 51:14.406
I was yelling at him
across the alley.

51:14.474 --> 51:17.576
And he got on
the phone to call for
reinforcements, and

51:19.612 --> 51:22.848
he must have seen somebody
drawing down on Thomas,

51:22.916 --> 51:27.586
'cause he fired
a few shots in
that direction.

51:32.092 --> 51:33.926
And his rifle jammed.

51:40.166 --> 51:41.100
That's when...

51:43.370 --> 51:45.070
That's when he got hit.

51:47.474 --> 51:49.041
Did our son suffer?

51:52.479 --> 51:54.246
No, ma'am.

51:54.314 --> 51:58.550
No, he was...
It all happened
real fast.

51:58.618 --> 52:01.120
My brother's life
was wasted over there.

52:04.524 --> 52:07.960
Your brother died
doing what he knew
in his heart was his duty.

52:09.963 --> 52:12.664
And he died
in the arms of
his best friend.

52:13.900 --> 52:16.068
I can tell you that.

52:16.136 --> 52:19.938
He's the one
that sent the picture
right after we lost Paul.

52:21.107 --> 52:23.008
Read the back.

52:23.076 --> 52:27.479
(PASTOR COLSON READING)

52:29.916 --> 52:32.685
He calls, sometimes,
late at night.
Mmm-hmm.

52:32.752 --> 52:34.586
I think he's
been drinking.

52:37.257 --> 52:38.657
You keep that.

52:40.160 --> 52:41.493
Thank you, sir,
I will.

52:41.561 --> 52:44.430
We want to thank you,
Sergeant King,
for coming.

52:44.497 --> 52:47.499
Because I know that
these meetings must be
very difficult for you.

52:47.567 --> 52:49.068
Yes, ma'am.
Thank you,
Sergeant.

52:49.135 --> 52:51.670
Thank you for coming.

52:51.738 --> 52:52.971
Thank you.

52:54.140 --> 52:55.974
Good luck
getting out.

53:03.383 --> 53:05.951
That was real nice,
what you did back there.

53:09.789 --> 53:12.224
So you wanna go find
this place Preacher's
brother told me about?

53:12.292 --> 53:15.094
I'm going straight to D.C.
End of discussion.

53:15.161 --> 53:16.528
All right.

53:23.436 --> 53:25.270
Damn.

53:25.338 --> 53:26.572
Wait here!
Brandon.

53:26.706 --> 53:27.706
Wait here!

53:29.342 --> 53:30.709
It don't matter.

53:55.735 --> 53:57.336
(MAN LAUGHING)

