01:13:22.068 --> 01:13:23.936
Swear to God.

01:13:24.004 --> 01:13:25.337
Just propose again.

01:13:25.405 --> 01:13:27.873
We'll get married again.

01:13:27.941 --> 01:13:30.342
Only thing you
proposing is to
get locked up, man.

01:13:30.410 --> 01:13:32.044
Let's get
out of here.

01:13:34.981 --> 01:13:36.782
All right.
Come on, man.

01:13:36.850 --> 01:13:39.184
You know I ain't gonna
let you go over there.
Let's go.

01:13:39.252 --> 01:13:40.486
You talking
about Jeanie?

01:13:40.553 --> 01:13:43.022
You can't even manage
your own woman.

01:13:48.361 --> 01:13:49.962
No, I didn't mean
it like that, Steve.
Steve.

01:13:50.030 --> 01:13:52.698
No, seriously.
No, come on.
Tommy. Tommy!

01:13:52.766 --> 01:13:55.000
I'm sorry.

01:13:55.068 --> 01:13:56.902
Steve, come on.
I'm sorry.

01:14:03.710 --> 01:14:05.511
(ALARM BLARING)

01:14:48.588 --> 01:14:50.422
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

01:15:06.272 --> 01:15:07.406
(GRUNTS)

01:15:19.386 --> 01:15:21.220
(GREETING IN SPANISH)

01:15:25.058 --> 01:15:27.826
I smell a woman,
and it ain't a nurse.

01:15:28.928 --> 01:15:29.828
Then who?

01:15:31.164 --> 01:15:32.498
<i>Hola, Private Rodriguez.</i>

01:15:32.565 --> 01:15:34.166
Sergeant King!

01:15:34.234 --> 01:15:36.301
My first visitor.

01:15:36.369 --> 01:15:37.736
You found me.

01:15:37.804 --> 01:15:39.638
I did.

01:15:39.706 --> 01:15:41.240
And who?

01:15:41.307 --> 01:15:42.474
Michelle.

01:15:44.377 --> 01:15:45.511
Hey, Rico.

01:15:46.913 --> 01:15:49.014
Sergeant
Shriver's Michelle.

01:15:51.918 --> 01:15:55.621
Sunny blonde hair,
green eyes.

01:15:55.689 --> 01:15:58.724
Steve showed us
your picture
a million times.

01:15:58.792 --> 01:16:02.795
Sergeant King came to see me
with his best friend's girl!

01:16:02.862 --> 01:16:04.396
(RICO CHUCKLES)

01:16:04.464 --> 01:16:05.464
It's a long story.

01:16:05.532 --> 01:16:06.799
Yes, sir,
I bet it is.

01:16:06.866 --> 01:16:10.469
Sit, man.
I got time.

01:16:10.537 --> 01:16:11.970
Good to see you.

01:16:12.038 --> 01:16:13.839
It's good to see you.

01:16:13.907 --> 01:16:15.674
How's my mother?

01:16:15.742 --> 01:16:17.643
She's good.
She's missing you.

01:16:17.711 --> 01:16:20.012
Yeah. And my brothers?

01:16:20.080 --> 01:16:22.047
They're getting big.
Growing up.

01:16:22.115 --> 01:16:24.216
They strong?
Seem to be.

01:16:24.284 --> 01:16:25.351
Taking after
their brother.

01:16:25.418 --> 01:16:27.720
Not as handsome.
Close.

01:16:27.787 --> 01:16:29.555
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

01:16:43.103 --> 01:16:44.803
I'll let you
guys talk.

01:16:44.871 --> 01:16:48.040
All right.
Thanks for
coming to see me.

01:16:48.108 --> 01:16:49.708
(BOTH LAUGH)
She sounds cute.

01:16:51.945 --> 01:16:55.147
How're you feeling?
Feeling good, sir.

01:16:55.215 --> 01:16:56.782
Just as comfy
as a Humvee.

01:16:56.950 --> 01:16:58.550
You think?

01:16:58.618 --> 01:17:00.085
I wouldn't have thought,
but...

01:17:00.153 --> 01:17:02.021
They taking good
care of you?

01:17:02.088 --> 01:17:03.989
First-class
treatment, Sarge.

01:17:04.057 --> 01:17:05.324
Good. So I don't have
to talk to anybody?

01:17:05.392 --> 01:17:06.458
No, sir.

01:17:06.526 --> 01:17:07.493
All right.

01:17:16.069 --> 01:17:17.369
Nice break.

01:17:17.437 --> 01:17:18.637
Thank you.

01:17:27.714 --> 01:17:28.814
(LAUGHS)

01:17:28.882 --> 01:17:30.049
That's impressive.

01:17:30.116 --> 01:17:31.383
Sloppy.

01:17:31.451 --> 01:17:33.185
What can I say?
You're in, though.

01:17:33.253 --> 01:17:35.154
Come on.
I think she's
a butter face.

01:17:35.221 --> 01:17:37.256
Yeah?
She's hot,
but her face.

01:17:37.323 --> 01:17:38.691
But does she
give a good bath?

01:17:38.758 --> 01:17:40.059
She's got
some soft hands.

01:17:40.126 --> 01:17:42.428
Well, there you go.
That's what matters.

01:17:42.495 --> 01:17:46.532
I haven't felt
anything else,
but that'll change.

01:17:46.599 --> 01:17:49.435
Soon as I get
the rest of this.
All right.

01:17:51.137 --> 01:17:55.107
Man, I had this thing,
like a dream, all right?

01:17:55.175 --> 01:17:57.509
You were at the bottom
of a swimming pool,

01:17:57.577 --> 01:18:00.245
and I dove in to
try to save you.

01:18:00.313 --> 01:18:01.780
But I couldn't.

01:18:02.816 --> 01:18:04.249
It's okay, man.

01:18:05.452 --> 01:18:06.752
You did save me.

01:18:08.588 --> 01:18:09.755
I'm right here.

01:18:11.891 --> 01:18:13.759
And seeing stuff, man?

01:18:15.662 --> 01:18:17.229
Here, at night?

01:18:19.065 --> 01:18:22.434
Sounds like
a fucking horror movie.

01:18:22.502 --> 01:18:25.337
Guys screaming,
nightmares...

01:18:28.441 --> 01:18:31.243
Sarge,
we got out
just in time.

01:18:33.513 --> 01:18:35.748
I mean,
Haji's new bombs...

01:18:37.417 --> 01:18:39.785
You don't want
to survive, man.

01:18:39.853 --> 01:18:42.921
Sounds crazy,
but I feel lucky,
you know?

01:18:45.392 --> 01:18:48.060
They want to send me back.

01:18:48.128 --> 01:18:50.696
I hope you told
them no fucking way.

01:18:51.798 --> 01:18:54.333
I mean,
I might go back.

01:18:54.401 --> 01:18:57.903
'Cause if I got killed,
my family would
get green cards.

01:19:04.544 --> 01:19:05.811
Sir.
Yeah?

01:19:05.879 --> 01:19:07.846
Could you move
me out of the sun?

01:19:07.914 --> 01:19:09.081
Okay.

01:19:16.322 --> 01:19:20.426
So, I'm sorry,
but I got to ask.

01:19:20.493 --> 01:19:24.096
What you doing
with Sergeant
Shriver's fiancee?

01:19:24.164 --> 01:19:26.598
They broke up.
She's just giving me
a ride.

01:19:29.102 --> 01:19:33.605
She was giving
you a ride before
or after they broke up?

01:19:33.673 --> 01:19:34.707
Not like that.

01:19:34.774 --> 01:19:36.608
Michelle's
close to my family.

01:19:36.676 --> 01:19:38.577
She's just helping me out.
She's somebody...

01:19:38.645 --> 01:19:40.479
(SHUSHING)

01:19:40.547 --> 01:19:41.313
(LAUGHS)
What?

01:19:44.651 --> 01:19:48.120
You should hear
the way you sound, Sarge.

01:19:48.188 --> 01:19:51.056
You a Jody.

01:19:51.124 --> 01:19:55.160
It's time for you to
go back to your room,
Private Rodriguez.

01:19:55.228 --> 01:19:57.663
# Jody got your girl
and gone #

01:19:57.731 --> 01:19:58.831
Sing it.

01:19:58.898 --> 01:20:00.432
I don't know
the words.
You sing it.

01:20:00.500 --> 01:20:04.570
# Ain't no use in going home
Jody got your girl and gone #

01:20:04.637 --> 01:20:07.339
You watching this one?
Mmm-hmm.

01:20:12.779 --> 01:20:14.780
Nice shot.
Now we're even.

01:20:16.850 --> 01:20:18.117
What you laughing at?
You lost.

01:20:24.224 --> 01:20:25.758
That's pretty funny.

01:20:25.825 --> 01:20:27.493
"Give you a hand."
Dumbass.

01:20:31.765 --> 01:20:33.165
Help me push it.
Yeah.

01:20:36.002 --> 01:20:37.236
Thank you.

01:20:44.377 --> 01:20:46.178
It's fucking strong.
Is it?

01:20:52.485 --> 01:20:53.952
I'll be in touch, Rico.

01:20:54.020 --> 01:20:55.220
Tell the boys I said,
"What's up?"

01:20:55.288 --> 01:20:56.689
I will.

01:21:07.967 --> 01:21:10.069
I signed up,

01:21:10.136 --> 01:21:13.172
thinking I was
gonna go over there
and protect my country.

01:21:13.239 --> 01:21:14.306
My family.

01:21:16.710 --> 01:21:19.578
We wanted
payback for 9/11,

01:21:19.646 --> 01:21:21.080
and you get there,

01:21:21.147 --> 01:21:24.616
and you realize
the war wasn't even
about any of that.

01:21:24.684 --> 01:21:26.018
The enemy ain't
out in the desert.

01:21:26.086 --> 01:21:30.389
They're in
the hallways and rooftops,
living rooms, kitchens.

01:21:31.925 --> 01:21:33.392
Everybody's got a weapon.

01:21:34.394 --> 01:21:35.494
Everybody.

01:21:35.562 --> 01:21:38.364
Nobody knows who's who.

01:21:38.431 --> 01:21:41.066
The only thing
you can believe in
is surviving.

01:21:41.134 --> 01:21:45.304
Protecting
the guy to your left
and the guy to your right.

01:21:45.372 --> 01:21:49.341
Side by side,
willing to die
for each other.

01:21:52.545 --> 01:21:54.847
By the time
you start seeing

01:21:56.683 --> 01:22:00.853
good friends'
bodies held together
by a belt after a car bomb,

01:22:04.090 --> 01:22:06.792
you get
a kill-or-be-killed
mentality.

01:22:18.738 --> 01:22:20.072
It's okay.

01:22:20.774 --> 01:22:21.874
No, it ain't.

01:22:25.779 --> 01:22:27.513
Michelle, I'm worried
if I tell you these things,

01:22:27.580 --> 01:22:30.549
you're gonna think
differently of me,
and I...

01:22:30.617 --> 01:22:33.218
I couldn't stand that.

01:22:33.286 --> 01:22:35.220
I ain't gonna
think that.

01:22:39.225 --> 01:22:40.092
(SIGHS)

01:22:41.728 --> 01:22:43.729
Our last mission,
in the alley,

01:22:43.797 --> 01:22:46.799
well, when Rico got hit,

01:22:46.866 --> 01:22:50.736
I looked in his face,
and most of it
was burned off.

01:22:55.275 --> 01:22:58.510
I had to go
in to get Steve.

01:22:58.578 --> 01:23:00.245
<i>I knew he</i>
<i>was in trouble.</i>

01:23:06.586 --> 01:23:08.287
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

01:23:41.654 --> 01:23:43.088
I'm done with killing.

01:23:43.156 --> 01:23:46.225
And I ain't leading
any more men into
a slaughter.

01:23:51.664 --> 01:23:53.032
You have to
call Carlson.

01:24:00.540 --> 01:24:01.507
I know.

01:24:15.588 --> 01:24:16.622
(SNIFFLES)

01:24:29.402 --> 01:24:30.502
Mr. Carlson.

01:24:31.905 --> 01:24:34.173
My name is...
<i>CARLSON: No names.</i>

01:24:34.240 --> 01:24:35.507
<i>All right.</i>
<i>What's the problem?</i>

01:24:37.277 --> 01:24:40.479
I'm a Staff Sergeant,
a squad leader,

01:24:40.547 --> 01:24:44.717
two tours,
Afghanistan and Iraq,
and I just got stop-lossed.

01:24:44.784 --> 01:24:46.885
They're shipping me back
at the end of the month.

01:24:46.953 --> 01:24:49.288
<i>There's so many of</i>
<i>you guys out there.</i>

01:24:49.356 --> 01:24:54.093
<i>I've heard it before.</i>
<i>It's the same story,</i>
<i>and you eventually call me.</i>

01:24:54.160 --> 01:24:56.295
<i>Do you understand what I do?</i>

01:24:56.363 --> 01:24:59.531
<i>I strip away who you are.</i>
<i>I set you down</i>
<i>in a foreign place</i>

01:24:59.599 --> 01:25:00.799
<i>where you're gonna live</i>
<i>the rest of your life</i>

01:25:00.867 --> 01:25:02.568
<i>pretending to</i>
<i>be someone else.</i>

01:25:02.635 --> 01:25:04.169
<i>Do you want that?</i>

01:25:04.237 --> 01:25:07.673
I can't go home.
I can't go back.
I got no other options.

01:25:10.477 --> 01:25:12.845
I need your services.

01:25:12.912 --> 01:25:16.281
<i>I won't be able to</i>
<i>discuss this further</i>
<i>over the phone.</i>

01:25:16.349 --> 01:25:18.283
<i>Do you have some money?</i>
<i>Like a grand?</i>

01:25:19.819 --> 01:25:21.720
I have a few bucks.

01:25:21.788 --> 01:25:25.157
<i>Well, when you get a grand,</i>
<i>start driving north</i>
<i>toward New York City.</i>

01:25:27.260 --> 01:25:31.363
700, 800, 900, 1000.

01:25:32.565 --> 01:25:34.033
Not a bad price.

01:25:34.100 --> 01:25:34.867
Thank you, sir.

01:26:21.348 --> 01:26:24.516
Come on.
This is a good
opportunity.

01:26:24.584 --> 01:26:27.820
Rainey said that
people will just line up
to buy a Cadillac from a vet.

01:26:27.887 --> 01:26:30.155
Yeah, not with a BCD.

01:26:30.223 --> 01:26:32.991
It's not like you're
gonna hang it on the
showroom wall, Tommy.

01:26:35.061 --> 01:26:36.562
What's a BCD?

01:26:38.565 --> 01:26:39.598
(SIGHS)

01:26:39.666 --> 01:26:41.266
It's the big
chicken dinner.

01:26:43.703 --> 01:26:45.437
It's what we
call it in the Army.

01:26:45.505 --> 01:26:47.139
It's a Bad
Conduct Discharge.

01:26:51.111 --> 01:26:53.145
We gonna shoot
this shit up, or what?

01:26:54.647 --> 01:26:55.547
That shotgun loaded?

01:26:57.283 --> 01:26:59.551
What's the first rule
of weapon safety, Tommy?

01:26:59.619 --> 01:27:01.987
Always assume
every weapon
is loaded.

01:27:03.189 --> 01:27:04.323
Yes, sir.

01:27:05.325 --> 01:27:06.258
Sorry.

01:27:07.627 --> 01:27:08.260
(CHUCKLES)

01:27:09.729 --> 01:27:11.096
Where are you going?

01:27:11.164 --> 01:27:13.565
I'm going back
to the bunkhouse,
write a hit song.

01:27:15.435 --> 01:27:18.604
# Don't feel like
shooting shit up today

01:27:18.672 --> 01:27:23.308
ALL: # 'Cause we'll put
a boot in your ass
It's the American way

01:27:23.376 --> 01:27:24.576
# Hey, Uncle Sam... #

01:27:26.079 --> 01:27:27.579
Later, guys.
All right, man.

01:27:27.647 --> 01:27:29.181
SHORTY: Later, Tommy.

01:27:29.249 --> 01:27:34.319
# Brought to you courtesy
of the red, white and blue

01:27:40.860 --> 01:27:43.262
# Of my red, white and blue #

01:27:56.242 --> 01:27:58.143
I spotted you guys
from a mile off.

01:28:00.213 --> 01:28:00.979
Oh, well.

01:28:02.182 --> 01:28:03.749
What happened?

01:28:03.817 --> 01:28:05.851
I just had a run-in
with a couple guys.

01:28:05.919 --> 01:28:08.921
Yeah.
That kind of shit happens
when you're on the run.

01:28:08.988 --> 01:28:11.523
All you guys get
popped eventually.

01:28:13.326 --> 01:28:14.793
Is this a package deal?

01:28:16.496 --> 01:28:18.330
Just one for now.

01:28:19.666 --> 01:28:20.799
You thought about this?

01:28:20.867 --> 01:28:22.201
Yes, sir.

01:28:22.268 --> 01:28:23.802
'Cause one-way
means one-way.

01:28:24.804 --> 01:28:26.672
You go,
you're going for good,

01:28:26.740 --> 01:28:28.774
unless you get
fucked with extradition.

01:28:28.842 --> 01:28:30.009
Pardon my French.

01:28:31.478 --> 01:28:33.178
I don't want you
calling me up crying

01:28:33.246 --> 01:28:35.647
how you can't go
to grandma's funeral
back in Tennessee.

01:28:35.715 --> 01:28:36.849
Texas.

01:28:37.951 --> 01:28:38.984
We're from Texas.

01:28:39.052 --> 01:28:41.387
(CLEARS THROAT) Whatever.

01:28:41.454 --> 01:28:43.856
I just want it all
laid out straight.

01:28:46.026 --> 01:28:48.360
Canada's not that bad.

01:28:48.428 --> 01:28:51.930
I just had a guy up there,
got married to
a real sweet local girl.

01:28:51.998 --> 01:28:53.565
Loves Toronto.

01:28:53.633 --> 01:28:56.301
Says it's a lot
like New York.

01:28:56.369 --> 01:28:58.637
I ain't so crazy
about New York, so far.

01:28:59.939 --> 01:29:01.674
You got any other options?

01:29:01.741 --> 01:29:03.475
Like, what about Mexico?

01:29:03.543 --> 01:29:05.277
Look, I don't know
shit about Mexico.

01:29:07.414 --> 01:29:09.548
Here's your new I.D.

01:29:09.616 --> 01:29:11.617
They'll fix in the photos
before you leave.

01:29:13.920 --> 01:29:17.322
Day after tomorrow,
somebody will meet you
at this address in Buffalo.

01:29:19.459 --> 01:29:20.726
Take you over.

01:29:21.961 --> 01:29:23.328
You got the money?

01:29:23.396 --> 01:29:24.563
MICHELLE: Here.

01:29:28.702 --> 01:29:30.369
No refunds, right?

01:29:30.437 --> 01:29:32.705
Got it.
Half now and half across.

01:29:35.041 --> 01:29:36.241
Go make your calls.

01:29:37.277 --> 01:29:38.377
Say your goodbyes.

01:29:49.522 --> 01:29:50.689
Hi, Mom?

01:29:55.328 --> 01:29:56.595
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:29:56.696 --> 01:29:57.696
He did what?

01:30:02.802 --> 01:30:03.669
When?

01:30:10.243 --> 01:30:11.643
I don't...

01:30:14.314 --> 01:30:16.181
Let me call you back, Mom.

01:30:18.218 --> 01:30:20.953
(BRANDON BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:30:25.458 --> 01:30:27.226
Tommy shot himself
out at the ranch.

01:30:35.235 --> 01:30:36.568
(GUN FIRES)

01:30:40.473 --> 01:30:41.573
(GUN FIRES)

01:30:44.577 --> 01:30:46.378
<i>(TAPS PLAYING)</i>

01:31:29.389 --> 01:31:30.789
OFFICER: Left, face.

01:31:34.994 --> 01:31:36.128
This flag

01:31:39.065 --> 01:31:42.134
is presented on behalf
of a grateful nation

01:31:44.437 --> 01:31:46.605
and the United States Army

01:31:47.907 --> 01:31:51.110
as a token of appreciation
for your loved one's

01:31:52.379 --> 01:31:55.114
honorable and
faithful service.

01:31:59.619 --> 01:32:00.786
(SIGHS)

01:32:18.872 --> 01:32:20.673
Come on, Ida.
Let's go.

01:32:25.245 --> 01:32:27.680
(SOBBING QUIETLY)

01:33:26.039 --> 01:33:27.606
Look who came home.

01:33:37.117 --> 01:33:38.150
(BRANDON COUGHING)

01:33:38.218 --> 01:33:40.019
That's for fucking
running out on us.

01:33:42.122 --> 01:33:44.423
And that's for coming
back too fucking late.

01:33:47.927 --> 01:33:49.762
And that's on
general principle.

01:33:52.298 --> 01:33:54.500
(COUGHING)

01:33:56.236 --> 01:33:57.536
Fuck you.

01:33:57.604 --> 01:34:00.639
You're throwing everything
in your life away.
You stupid...

01:34:01.741 --> 01:34:02.975
(GRUNTS)

01:34:05.445 --> 01:34:07.346
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:34:14.454 --> 01:34:16.155
Y'all gonna get
yourselves killed,
you know that?

01:34:16.222 --> 01:34:17.890
Do you hear me?

01:34:19.859 --> 01:34:20.959
Shut the fuck up.

01:34:32.806 --> 01:34:36.041
So you just go
over there and you do
your fucking duty.

01:34:37.444 --> 01:34:38.344
You see this?

01:34:39.746 --> 01:34:40.779
You see this?

01:34:41.648 --> 01:34:43.282
This is you next.

01:34:47.620 --> 01:34:49.455
(BOTH COUGHING)

01:35:06.606 --> 01:35:08.674
(BOTH PANTING)

01:35:25.225 --> 01:35:26.725
Steve.

